ğŸ“‹ File Descriptions
Core Scripts
heart_disease_detective.py

Purpose: Main analysis script with complete pipeline
Features: Data cleaning, normalization, Bayesian network construction, inference
Usage: python heart_disease_detective.py
Output: All analysis results and visualizations

heart_disease_analysis.ipynb

Purpose: Interactive Jupyter notebook version
Features: Step-by-step analysis with explanations
Usage: jupyter notebook heart_disease_analysis.ipynb
Benefits: Educational, interactive, cell-by-cell execution

Data Files
heart_disease.csv (Original Dataset)
Columns: age, sex, cp, trestbps, chol, fbs, restecg, thalach, exang, oldpeak, slope, ca, thal, target
Rows: ~300 patient records
Target: Binary heart disease indicator (0/1)
cleaned_heart_disease.csv (Processed)

Duplicates removed
Missing values handled
Data types standardized

normalized_heart_disease.csv (Normalized)

Min-max scaling applied to numeric features
Target variable preserved
Ready for machine learning

discretized_heart_disease.csv (Bayesian Ready)

Continuous variables binned into categories
Optimal for Bayesian network modeling
Simplified inference computation

Generated Reports
analysis_report.md
markdown# Comprehensive Analysis Report
- Dataset statistics
- Cleaning results
- Model performance
- Clinical insights
- Recommendations
analysis_summary.md
markdown# Quick Summary
- Key findings
- Risk assessments
- Model validation
- Generated files
Visualizations
bayesian_network_structure.png

Network topology diagram
Node relationships
Probabilistic dependencies
Medical domain structure

inference_results.png

Probability distribution plots
Risk assessment charts
Comparative analysis
Clinical interpretation aids

ğŸ”§ Setup and Installation
Method 1: Automated Setup
bashpython setup.py
This will:

Check Python version compatibility
Install all required packages
Create directory structure
Download dataset (with instructions)
Verify installation

Method 2: Manual Setup
bash# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Download dataset
# Visit: https://bit.ly/3T1A7Rs
# Save as: heart_disease.csv

# Run analysis
python heart_disease_detective.py
Method 3: Development Setup
bash# Clone repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd heart-disease-detective

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install in development mode
pip install -e .
ğŸ¯ Usage Patterns
For Quick Analysis
bashpython heart_disease_detective.py

Complete analysis in one command
All outputs generated automatically
Perfect for production runs

For Interactive Exploration
bashjupyter notebook heart_disease_analysis.ipynb

Step-by-step execution
Modify parameters on the fly
Educational and experimental

For Custom Development
pythonfrom heart_disease_detective import HeartDiseaseDetective

detective = HeartDiseaseDetective('heart_disease.csv')
detective.load_data()
detective.clean_data()
# ... custom analysis steps
ğŸ“Š Output Files Guide
Data Outputs

Cleaned Data: data/cleaned_heart_disease.csv
Normalized Data: data/normalized_heart_disease.csv
Model-Ready Data: data/discretized_heart_disease.csv

Visualization Outputs

Network Structure: visualizations/bayesian_network_structure.png
Inference Results: visualizations/inference_results.png
Risk Assessments: visualizations/risk_assessment_charts.png

Report Outputs

Comprehensive Report: reports/analysis_report.md
Summary Report: reports/analysis_summary.md
Clinical Insights: reports/clinical_insights.md
